column6: Transmission error is  occurred between DX100 and laser sensor unit.
column7:
(1)Reset the alarm, and then try again.

(4)Replace JANCD-YCP01 board and the cable.

column5: Abnormalities have occurred at the thermostat of a laser head.
column6: The abnormalities of a laser head, the abnormalities of a cable
column7:
(1) Turn off the power supply of a robot controller and NCL01 unit. 
(2) Check whether the laser head has carried out unusual generation of heat. 
(3) Check whether there are any abnormalities in the I/O cable between NCL01 unit and a laser head. 
(4) Check whether there are any abnormalities in the thermostat and cable of a laser head.

column5: Abnormalities have occurred in LVDS of a laser head.

(3)Check whether there are any abnormalities in the LVDS cable between NCL01 unit and a laser head.

column5: The abnormalities of a CAN signal.

(2) Check whether YCP02 substrate and YSL02 substrate are connected correctly.
